Her departure, announced on Wednesday, comes amidst a challenging period for Musk, though no specific reasons for her exit were provided. Yaccarino, who joined X shortly after Musk's acquisition and renaming of the platform formerly known as Twitter, expressed pride in the team's achievements during her tenure. There has been no announcement regarding her successor.
